Node.Notes: Literally "young women." Probably the musical tune/setting to which the psalm was sung.

Coming first, "they roar," is vague in referent and meaning. The next clause supplies the referent and semantic context, so that it is known that the roaring and foaming point to the violent fury of waves.
Events evoking terror/horror/astonishment from those who see it. In this case, probably desolation/devastation. Some go with "wonders/amazing things" in a positive sense, following the LXX.
